metadata.name: Digital Gardens #246
metadata.description:
Digital Gardens are places of magic and wonder, where you can connect with your inner nature and take a deep breath. Digital Gardens are a refuge from the world outside. A sanctuary for the mind, body, and soul. But they are also a place of play and exploration. It is a space where you can let your imagination run wild, creating and discovering new things.
Digital Gardens brings to life the minimalistic essence of Detegus‚Äô art and the abstract and rational art of Alfredo Boaron.
The gardens are generated from a recursive function dividing the space at each iteration with a proportion that follows the Fibonacci succession and randomly stops after some iterations. At each recursion the canvas is divided into two pieces following the proportion of two consecutive Fibonacci numbers [1 to 144].
The minimalistic visual effect is then personalized by the palettes of 15 artists who embraced the invitation to give their personal contribution to the collection. The palette name and the author name is displayed in the features along with the Fibonacci numbers ratio, the colors number vs the total palette color number, the background color, the total number of rectangles and the depth level of recursion achieved by the algorithm.
Immerse yourself in this generative project, inspired by geometrism and abstract expressionism. 
Lose yourself in the beauty of a digital garden.

metadata.name: Twistings #140
metadata.description:
‚úß TWISTINGS ‚úß

Twistings, the "Explore Variety" collection, explores the beauty & variety that is hidden within the simple math of Archimedean spirals.

There are seven different circular "entities", each brought forward by using slightly different mathematical settings of the spiral formulas: Drops, Circles, Fireworks, Flowers, Roses, Spirals & Twisters.

____

‚úß CURATED / RANDOM ‚úß

I love both the concept of a heavily curated set, hand picked by the artist, the best representation / the most beautiful, but also the concept of the larger, random collections showing the variety hidden within the algorithm.

I've therefore also released an "Artist Curated" collection of 7 pieces that I meticulously hand-picked from over 1000 outputs. You can find these on the platform 1stDibs.com/nft (under my name "nadieh"). They represent my favorite for each of the seven unique entities. A free mint of this "Explore Variety" collection will be airdropped to each buyer of a "Curated" piece.

____

‚úß OPTIONS ‚úß

n - Toggle grainy noise on/off (on by default, it's subtle to see)

s - Save the image at the current window size and pixel density

To save a larger image you can add the parameter `&pixeldensity=2` (or another number) to the end of the URL when viewed on the live page. Afterwards press "s" to save the image. The number is the factor with which the width and height are increased w.r.t. the current window size.

-- The larger the image / pixeldensity, the longer it will take to create & save --

____

‚úß NOTES ‚úß

It works best and fastest in Firefox!

As of the drop day there is a browser bug for Chrome on the ARM Apple laptops. It incorrectly visualizes certain color blend modes. The following color palettes are affected: Antique, Camping, Pastel, Prime & Rainbow. I hope/assume this will be fixed soon. 

____

Created by Nadieh Bremer
Twitter & Instagram: @NadiehBremer
Website: VisualCinnamon.com

metadata.name: In Due Time #164
metadata.description:
‚ÄúIn Due Time‚Äù is a collaborative generative collection between artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria. Inspired by Wiederrecht‚Äôs mastery of line and Vittoria‚Äôs notable palette, this 1/1/250 series captures the present moment. It serves as a reminder that we are more similar than we are different, leveraging homogeneous shapes to create distinctive compositions.

Vittoria‚Äôs poem for the collection:

‚ÄúIn Due Time‚Äù
We will all become
Particles dancing
Across the skyline.

The artwork listed is indeed authentic, created by, and copyright to artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria; the purchase of this NFT is a purchase of the asset, not of the copyright.

-------------------------------------------

To save a high-resolution image for printing, click ‚Äúopen‚Äù under the image on the page for your token, and then hit:

Digits ‚Äú1‚Äù through ‚Äú9‚Äù to get an image that is 1000 through 9000px tall.  This may take a while, depending on the size and your computer, so please be patient.

metadata.name: Landscapes out of my mind #192
metadata.description:
In this work, the third in the series of landscapes, I tried to achieve greater realism without abandoning those elements, also characteristic of the other works, which lead out of reality such as the shapes of the ground and trees and the choice of palettes.

Lands and Clouds are rendered using a mix of simplex noise and FBM (Fractional Brownian Motion), trees are generated with space colonization algorithm an placed using Poisson Disk Sampling distribution. The distribution density is driven by the land heightmap.


Developed with three.js using WebGLRenderer.
Rendering is faster with chrome browser.


[s] to save a png at 2048x1536, 1536x2048, 2048x2048 (4/3, 3/4, 4/4 aspect ratio)
[d] to save a png at 4096x3072, 3072x4096, 4096x4096 (4/3, 3/4, 4/4 aspect ratio)


Features:
"Palette": 14 colormaps
"Aspect Ratio": 4/3, 3/4, 4/4
"View Point":  Far, Medium, Near, Above
"Sky Type": FBM, Gradient1, Gradient2
"Sky Color": LightSkyBlue, Gray, Blue [10% probability]
"Bark Color":  Brown, GrayBrown, Gray
"Bare Trees": True, False


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.description: This work is a research of flow fields, exploring generative art forms and colors. It uses various drawing methods, randomized color palettes, and layers of patterns to add multiple dimensions of variety to the work. Willing to create a visual blossom.

metadata.name: Ridge Blur #167
metadata.description:
This work is the second in the ridge series. While using the same base algorithm this work is about exploring landscapes using a much more dark and desolate imagery.

It was designed to be experienced in fullscreen in live mode.
Press "s" to save a screenshot.

Dutch auction (14/11/8), updating every 5min.

Original artwork by William Watkins ¬∑ Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Ridge Scribbles #91
metadata.description:
Ridge scribbles is the first piece of a small series around mountain landscapes using different rendering techniques.

A heightmap is generated using fractal noise with different parameters and scales. Then we generate tens of thousands of paths by using a gradient descent algorithm with momentum, starting at random positions on the reversed heightmap. Those paths are then rendered using one of 11 different colour palettes.

Press "s" to save a screenshot.

Original artwork by William Watkins ¬∑ Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Dancing Dots #27
metadata.description:
Dancing Dots is a study on coordinated movements and non-affine transforms chaining. The resulting moving dots sequences are unique and relaxing to watch.

The features available in this series are:
- Sequence_Length: Number of different steps in the sequence
- Grid_Size: the size of the grid, obviously
- Dots_Shape: either circles (common) or squares (rare)
- Contour_Line: a small line between each corner dots (uncommon)
- Blurry: A blurry/ trailing effect (rare)
- Color Palette: Rainbow (common), Bicolor (common), Monochrome (rare) or ... a very rare surprise.
